trend_summary: Across the image sequence, scattered single-family housing slowly fills wooded plots, with small clearings enlarging and a few new driveways and local roads added. Forest cover declines slightly, but the area retains a heavily treed, low-intensity residential character without major commercial or industrial growth.
notable_changes: Gradual increase in individual house rooftops, especially near the central spine road.
New short roads and driveways branch off existing streets, indicating incremental subdivision.
Tree canopy recedes in several pockets where new lawns and clearings appear.
No significant expansion of commercial or industrial footprints observed.
Overall road network remains largely unchanged, with minor surface widening in places.
